cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless network carriers and device-to-device communication, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) - The paper formulates the tension between carrier and end-users as a Stackelberg game and explores the equilibrium points, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper utilizes dynamic pricing schemes and explores the impact of uncertainty on the system's performance, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper explores the impact of end-users' activity patterns on the carrier's profit and end-users' expected payments, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes a novel marketplace and explores the impact of different pricing schemes on the carrier's profit and end-users' expected payments, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
